  "title": "Executive Chef – Cantonese Cuisine / Central",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Develop menus and plating in line with the Head Executive Chef’s direction</p></li><li><p>Work with the Executive Chef on pricing and menu strategies to drive revenue</p></li><li><p>Maintain high standards of food quality, consistency, and presentation</p></li><li><p>Control food costs, inventory, and kitchen expenses</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with kitchen SOPs, hygiene, and food safety standards</p></li><li><p>Oversee daily kitchen operations, manpower planning, and scheduling</p></li><li><p>Lead, train, and supervise kitchen staff; conduct appraisals and coaching</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with front-of-house teams to ensure smooth service</p></li><li><p>Handle customer feedback and special requests professionally</p></li><li><p>Perform other duties as assigned</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li>Experience in Cantonese or Chinese cuisine (leadership role preferred)</li><li>Strong culinary foundation in Cantonese techniques</li><li>Proven experience leading and mentoring a kitchen team</li><li>Excellent understanding of food costing, supplier management, and kitchen operations</li><li>Strong leadership, communication, and problem-solving skills</li></ul><p>If you are interested, please send your resume to <strong>lucas.chang@swiftsearchglobal.com</strong> or whatsapp/call - <strong>9339 2324</strong></p><p>EA Personnel Name: Lucas Chang<br />EA Personnel No: R1874043<br />EA License No: 18C9495</p>",
